sentences.english: Only few States continue to maintain a separate chancery court.
sentences.chinese: 只有少數幾個州繼續保持獨立的衡平法院。

sentences.english: From the mountain peak we commanded a view of three States.
sentences.chinese: 從山頂我們可以眺三個州。

sentences.english: One possibility: tapping state disability funds.
sentences.chinese: 一種可能就是利用州傷病基金。

sentences.english: Perak, Malaysia is currently the police are stepping into the cause.

sentences.english: Similarly, state and county boundaries can be represented with polygons.
sentences.chinese: 類似地，州和國家邊界可以用多邊形表示。

sentences.english: It also covers in detail state appellate decisions construing the policy provisions.
sentences.chinese: 還包括詳細的解釋政策條款的州上訴決議。

sentences.english: This achievement led to the establishment of what was to become the renowned Connecticut clock-making industry.
sentences.chinese: 這項成就爲康乃狄克州打造出名聲卓越的鐘表工業。

sentences.english: By 1916, more than half the states held presidential primaries.
sentences.chinese: 到1916年，有半數以上的州舉行總統初選。

sentences.english: Maine is the only state that has a one-syllable name.

sentences.english: By 1936, only a dozen states continued to hold presidential primaries.
sentences.chinese: 到1936年，只有十來個州繼續舉行總統初選。

sentences.english: The Education Department said coaching was 'a private matter for parents'.
sentences.chinese: 州教育部說補習是家長們私人的事務。

sentences.english: Wooing the Granite State is fiendishly hard.
sentences.chinese: 要贏得“花崗岩州”有如過刀山下火海。

sentences.english: 1818- Illinois becomes the 21st U. S. state.
sentences.chinese: 1818年，伊利諾斯州成爲美國的第21州。

sentences.english: It was admitted as the 21st state in 1818.
sentences.chinese: 1818年作爲第二十一個州加入美國。

sentences.english: Remember the water-conserving toilets that many states started requiring about 30 years ago?
sentences.chinese: 記得許多州對提出要求是在30年前嗎？

sentences.english: The grand jury has been abolished in England and in approximately one-half of the states in the U. S.
sentences.chinese: 大陪審團在英國以及美國大部分州已經被廢除了。
